{
  "texts": [
    "Sentiment analysis.",
    "To address how affect is used in TED Talks compared with other science communication media, we relied on a dictionary-based approach (Denecke, 2008), a common approach to sentiment analysis (Feldman, 2013; Medhat et al. 2014).",
    "The approach involves mapping, wherever possible, the words in a text-in this case, the talk transcripts-to their corresponding sentiment value in the dictionary and calculating the sums of these values.",
    "In contrast to previous approaches, which often made use of the proprietary Linguistic Inquiry and Word Count (LIWC) database (e.g., Berger and Milkman, 2012; Brady et al. 2017; Hwong et al. 2017; Milkman and Berger, 2014), we relied on the openly available SentiWordNet sentiment dictionary (Baccianella et al. 2010).",
    "SentiWordNet contains more than 20,000 words with affect values ranging from -1 (most negative) to 1 (most positive)."
  ]
}